Class SanitizedArg

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.args.Arg
      • com.facebook.buck.rules.args.SanitizedArg
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RuleKeyAppendable

    public class SanitizedArg
extends Arg
    An Arg which must be sanitized before contributing to a RuleKey. 

     
 ImmutableMap<String, String> toolchainRoots =
     ImmutableMap.of("/opt/toolchain", "$TOOLCHAIN_ROOT");
 Path toolchainRoot = Paths.get("/opt/toolchain");
 Arg arg =
     new SanitizedArg(
         Functions.forMap(toolchainRoots),
         "/opt/toolchain/bin/tool");

        public void appendToCommandLine(com.google.common.collect.ImmutableCollection.Builder<String> builder)
        Description copied from class: Arg
        Append the contents of the Arg to the supplied builder. This call may inject any number of elements (including zero) into the builder. This is only ever safe to call when the rule is running, as it may do things like resolving source paths.
